-- Slovenia, U.S. Tied 2-2 in Second Half of World Cup Game in Johannesburg
-- Bob Bensch
-- 2010-06-18T15:46:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-18/slovenia-u-s-tied-2-2-in-second-half-of-world-cup-game-in-johannesburg.html

          
          
             (Corrects country in second paragraph.)  
 The U.S. has rallied to tie Slovenia
2-2 in the second half of their World Cup Group C game in
Johannesburg.  
 Landon Donovan and Michael Bradley have scored for the U.S.
in the second half. Valter Birsa and Zlatan Ljubijankic scored
for Slovenia in the first half.  
 The U.S. tied England 1-1 in its opening game and Slovenia
beat Algeria 1-0. England faces Algeria later today. Serbia
defeated Germany 1-0 earlier in Group D.  
          
          


  


        